    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> into thin wedges</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> pasta </strong>for an initial 7-8 min</p><p>Tip: This will finish cooking in your sauce later!</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[70ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span>of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>harissa stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until the garlic has slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>diced pollock</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p><p>Once the garlic has slightly softened, add the <strong>diced pollock</strong> to the pan with the<strong> tomato</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min or until the fish begins to turn opaque</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly opaque, add the<strong> drained pasta </strong>to the pan with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, the <strong>harissa stock</strong>, <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and increase the heat to high, then cook for 1-2 min further or until the sauce has slightly reduced and the fish is beginning to break up \u2013 this is your <strong>garlicky harissa pollock & tomato linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlicky-harissa-pollock-and-tomato-wholewheat-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlicky harissa pollock & tomato linguine </strong>with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
